loc <- h5read(input, name = "Locations")
H5close()

Full plots here

F0 as number on side

Here the F0 featrue is calculated from the z-scored data and printed as a number on teh right hand side of the plot.

## Calculate feature F0
F0 <- 
  foreach(j = 1:dim(dat)[1]) %:%
  foreach(i = 1:dim(dat)[2]) %do% {
      f0 <- sum(dat[j,i,,,])
}

names(F0) <- 1:length(F0)
for(i in 1:length(F0)){
  names(F0[[i]]) <- cnames
}


rr <- foreach(l = 1:dim(dat)[1]) %do% {
  r <- dat[l,,,,]
  mr <- melt(r)
  names(mr) <- c("ch", "x", "y", "z", "value")
  mr$z <- mr$z - (max(mr$z) +1)/2

  F0z <- Reduce('rbind', 
           lapply(names(F0[[l]]), 
             function(n){
             Fz <- mr[mr$ch == n,]
             #Fz$z <- as.numeric(max(mr$z)+1)
             Fz$F0 <- round(as.numeric(F0[[l]][n]),4)
             Fz
             }))

  #mr <- rbind(mr, F0z)
  #ch <- mr$ch
  #mr$type <- ctype$type[ch]
  #mr$ch <- abcnames[ch]
  #mr
  ch <- F0z$ch
  F0z$type <- ctype$type[ch]
  F0z$ch <- abcnames[ch]
  F0z
}


names(rr) <- 1:length(rr)


th <- theme(axis.text = element_blank(), axis.ticks = element_blank(),
            axis.title.y = element_blank(), axis.title.x = element_blank(),
            legend.position="bottom", legend.key.size = unit(2,'lines'),
            panel.spacing = unit(0, "lines"))

mmex <- min(sapply(rr, function(am){ min(am[am$type == "ex",]$value) }))
MMex <- max(sapply(rr, function(am){ max(am[am$type == "ex",]$value) }))
mmin <- min(sapply(rr, function(am){ min(am[am$type == "in",]$value) }))
MMin <- max(sapply(rr, function(am){ max(am[am$type == "in",]$value) }))
mmot <- min(sapply(rr, function(am){ min(am[am$type == "ot",]$value) }))
MMot <- max(sapply(rr, function(am){ max(am[am$type == "ot",]$value) }))

ggp <- list()
for(k in 1:length(rr)){
  mr <- rr[[k]]
  pex <- 
  ggplot(mr[mr$type == "ex",], 
    aes(x,y, group = factor(type), fill = value)) +
    geom_raster() + 
    scale_y_reverse() + 
    facet_grid(ch + F0 ~ z, labeller = label_both) +
    scale_fill_gradient(low = "black", high = "green", limits = c(mmex,MMex)) + th
  
  pin <- 
  ggplot(mr[mr$type == "in",], 
    aes(x,y, group = factor(type), fill = value)) +
    geom_raster() + 
    scale_y_reverse() + 
    facet_grid(ch + F0 ~ z, labeller = label_both) +
    scale_fill_gradient(low = "black", high = "red", limits = c(mmin,MMin)) + th
  
  pot <- 
    ggplot(mr[mr$type == "ot",], 
    aes(x,y, group = factor(type), fill = value)) +
    geom_raster() +
    scale_y_reverse() + 
    facet_grid(ch + F0 ~ z, labeller = label_both) +
    scale_fill_gradient(low = "black", high = "blue", limits = c(mmot,MMot)) + th
  #
  
  lay <- rbind(matrix(1,table(type)['ex'],1), 
        matrix(2,table(type)['in'],1), 
        matrix(3,table(type)['ot'],1))

  xyzloc = c(x = loc[k,1], 
          y = loc[k,2], 
          z = loc[k,3])

  p <- arrangeGrob(pex, pin, pot, layout_matrix = lay)

  ggp[[k]] <- list(xyzloc=xyzloc, p=p, pex=pex, pin=pin, pot=pot)
}

save(ggp, file = "F0num.RData")

mapply(function(grob,locs){
  outName <- paste0("num",token,
               paste0(c("x", "y", "z"),locs, collapse="_"),
               ".png")
  png(outName, 
      height = sum(tab)*1.5, width = dim(dat)[5]*1.5, 
      units = "in", res = 300)
  plot(grob)
  dev.off()},
  lapply(ggp, '[[', 2), lapply(ggp, '[[', 1))

F0 as a matrix :X:

Here I compute F0 as above and join a matrix to the z = 6 slot that is full of the same F0 value. The F0 value is much larger than the pixel values and overshadows the colorbar.

## Calculate feature F0
F0 <- 
  foreach(j = 1:dim(dat)[1]) %:%
  foreach(i = 1:dim(dat)[2]) %do% {
      #f0 <- matrix(sum(dat[j,i,,,]), 2*bf +1, 2*bf +1)
      f0 <- sum(dat[j,i,,,])
}

names(F0) <- 1:length(F0)
for(i in 1:length(F0)){
  names(F0[[i]]) <- cnames
}

rr <- foreach(l = 1:dim(dat)[1]) %do% {
  r <- dat[l,,,,]
  mr <- melt(r)
  names(mr) <- c("ch", "x", "y", "z", "value")
  mr$z <- mr$z - (max(mr$z) +1)/2
  mz <- min(mr$z)
  Mz <- max(mr$z)

  F0z <- Reduce('rbind', 
           lapply(names(F0[[l]]), 
             function(n){
             Fz <- mr[mr$ch == n,]
             Fz$z <- "F0" #as.numeric(max(mr$z)+1)
             Fz$value <- as.numeric(F0[[l]][n])
             Fz
             }))

  mr <- rbind(mr, F0z)
  ch <- mr$ch
  mr$type <- ctype$type[ch]
  mr$ch <- as.factor(abcnames[ch])
  mr$z <- factor(mr$z, levels = c(as.character(mz:Mz), "F0"))
  mr
  #ch <- F0z$ch
  #F0z$type <- ctype$type[ch]
  #F0z$ch <- abcnames[ch]
  #F0z
}


names(rr) <- 1:length(rr)


th <- theme(axis.text = element_blank(), axis.ticks = element_blank(),

            legend.position="bottom", legend.key.size = unit(2,'lines'),
            panel.spacing = unit(0, "lines"))

MMot <- max(sapply(rr, function(am){ max(am[am$type == "ot",]$value) }))

F0 averaged :X:

Here I compute F0 as above and average it by the number of pixels = 1331 in each cube and add it as a matrix same as above.

Because most of the pixels values are small, this doesnt seem to be visually helpful either.

## Calculate feature F0
F0 <- 
  foreach(j = 1:dim(dat)[1]) %:%
  foreach(i = 1:dim(dat)[2]) %do% {
      #f0 <- matrix(sum(dat[j,i,,,]), 2*bf +1, 2*bf +1)
      f0 <- sum(dat[j,i,,,])/1331
}

names(F0) <- 1:length(F0)

  names(F0[[i]]) <- cnames

Here I am plotting the data squished to 0-1, then I calculate the F0 value on the squished data and then plot F0 squished to 0-1.

## Calculate feature F0
F0 <- 
  foreach(j = 1:dim(datS)[1]) %:%
  foreach(i = 1:dim(datS)[2]) %do% {
      #f0 <- matrix(sum(dat[j,i,,,]), 2*bf +1, 2*bf +1)
      f0 <- sum(datS[j,i,,,])
}

F0S <- lapply(F0, function(y){
         x <- as.numeric(y)
         (x - min(x))/(max(x) - min(x))
  })

names(F0S) <- 1:length(F0S)
for(i in 1:length(F0S)){
  names(F0S[[i]]) <- cnames
}

rr <- foreach(l = 1:dim(dat)[1]) %do% {
  r <- datS[l,,,,]
  mr <- melt(r)
  names(mr) <- c("ch", "x", "y", "z", "value")
  mr$z <- mr$z - (max(mr$z) +1)/2

  F0z <- Reduce('rbind', 
           lapply(names(F0S[[l]]), 
             function(n){
             Fz <- mr[mr$ch == n,]
             Fz$z <- "F0_0-1"#as.numeric(max(mr$z)+1)
             Fz$value <- as.numeric(F0S[[l]][n])
             Fz
             }))

  mr <- rbind(mr, F0z)
  ch <- mr$ch
  mr$type <- ctype$type[ch]
  mr$ch <- as.factor(abcnames[ch])
  mr
  #ch <- F0z$ch
  #F0z$type <- ctype$type[ch]
  #F0z$ch <- abcnames[ch]
  #F0z
}

## Calculate feature F0
F0 <- 
  foreach(j = 1:dim(dat)[1]) %:%
  foreach(i = 1:dim(dat)[2]) %do% {
      f0 <- sum(dat[j,i,,,])

names(F0) <- 1:length(F0)
for(i in 1:length(F0)){
  names(F0[[i]]) <- cnames
}


rr <- foreach(l = 1:dim(dat)[1]) %do% {
  r <- dat[l,,,,]
  mr <- melt(r)
  names(mr) <- c("ch", "x", "y", "z", "value")
  mr$z <- mr$z - (max(mr$z) +1)/2

  F0z <- Reduce('rbind', 
           lapply(names(F0[[l]]), 
             function(n){
             Fz <- mr[mr$ch == n,]
             #Fz$z <- as.numeric(max(mr$z)+1)
             Fz$F0 <- round(as.numeric(F0[[l]][n]),4)
             Fz
             }))

  #mr <- rbind(mr, F0z)
  #ch <- mr$ch
  #mr$type <- ctype$type[ch]
  #mr$ch <- abcnames[ch]
  #mr
  ch <- F0z$ch
  F0z$type <- ctype$type[ch]
  F0z$ch <- abcnames[ch]
  F0z

      scale_y_reverse() + 
      facet_grid(ch +F0 ~ type, labeller = label_both) +
      scale_fill_gradient(low = "black", high = "white") + th

  laysep <- c()
  kj <- 1
  for(i in seq(1,5,2)){
    inner <- c()
    for(j in 1:table(type)[kj]){
      inner <- rbind(inner, c(rep(i, lz),rep(i+1,2)))
    }
  kj <- kj +1
  laysep <- rbind(laysep, inner)
  }

  psep <- arrangeGrob(pex, pexF0, pin, pinF0, pot, potF0, layout_matrix = laysep)

  ggpsep[[k]] <- list(xyzloc=xyzloc, p=psep, 
                   pex=pex, pexF0=pexF0,

                   pot=pot, potF0=potF0)
}
